The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, July 01, 2004 				 Race for BSNL top job hots up
 M RAJENDRAN 																								New Delhi, June 30: The Public Sector Enterprises Board (PSEB) has shortlisted 32 candidates for the post of chairman and managing director of Bharat Sanchar Nigam Ltd (BSNL). The interview for the post of CMD of the largest telecom company and leading public sector unit will be held on Tuesday and Wednesday. 																								The frontrunners include S.D Saxena, BSNLs director (finance), A. K. Saxena, adviser in the department of telecommunications (DoT), A. K. Chaturvedi, BSNL chief general manager (north), A. K. Sinha, BSNLs senior deputy director general, A. K. Bhandari, BSNL general manager (Gujarat), R. . Prabahkar, DoTs senior deputy director-general (value-added services), Rakesh Kumar, DoTs senior deputy director-general (services), and R. . Dubey, executive director of Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd (MTNL).																								The only non-departmental candidate in the fray is Rajneesh Gupta, an Indian Telecom Service (ITS) officer, currently chairman and managing director of Minerals and Engineering Corporation Ltd. Gupta was director of Videsh Sanchar Nigam in Calcutta but had opted for voluntary retirement when the government sold its majority stake to the Tatas following the disinvestment process.																								At present, BSNL is managed by V. P. Sinha as officiating CMD. His tenure ended today but is likely to be extended for another three months till the new candidate is selected. 																								Sinha is out of the race for a permanent appointment as CMD of the company since he is slated to retire in November. According to the governments rules, a candidate for the senior post of public sector company should have a minimum two years to go before retirement. 
